---
// Trials documents — true copies of the player-facing field documents.
// PLAYER-SAFE ONLY: no passwords, no hints, no book titles, no operator
// material. The full coordinate blocks live on the downloadable field guide
// (puzzle inputs, not answers) and the cards handed out at camp.
import TrialsLayout from "../../layouts/TrialsLayout.astro";
const crumbs = [
  { href: "/trials/", label: "← Trials" },
  { href: "/schedule/", label: "Event schedule →" },
];
---

<TrialsLayout
  title="Documents · Vibecamp Trials"
  description="Copies of every Vibecamp Trials handout, in one place."
  crumbs={crumbs}
>
  <header class="trials-hero">
    <p class="kicker">✦ Vibecamp Trials</p>
    <h1>Documents</h1>
    <p class="trials-sub">Every handout, in one place — lost your paper copy? It's here.</p>
  </header>

  <p class="dl-row">
    <a class="dl-btn" href="/trials/vibecamp-trials-field-guide.pdf" download>
      ⬇ Download the printable field guide <span class="dl-meta">(PDF · 2 pages)</span>
    </a>
  </p>

  <div class="board">

  <section class="doc-group" style="--ac: var(--green)">
  <div class="doc-intro pinned" style="--tilt: 0.4deg; --p1: #e4efdc; --p2: #d7e5cb">
    <p>
      ⛰️ <b>The Trial of Earth</b> — the camp map is on the
      <a href="/schedule/">schedule site</a>, and in interactive form at
      <a href="https://my.vibe.camp/#%7B%22currentView%22%3A%22Map%22%7D" target="_blank" rel="noopener">my.vibe.camp</a>.
      The cartographer stands by every line of it. Mostly.
    </p>
  </div>

  <article class="doc doc-survey pinned" id="erratum" style="--tilt: -0.7deg">
    <header class="doc-head">
      <span class="doc-tag">FIELD COPY</span>
      <h2>The Surveyor's Erratum</h2>
      <p class="doc-sub">OFFICE OF THE CARTOGRAPHER · CAMP RAMBLEWOOD COMMISSION · REV. 5</p>
    </header>
    <div class="doc-body">
      <p>
        The commissioned map of Camp Ramblewood is, in the cartographer's
        professional opinion, complete. Every road, every cabin, every venue.
        The cartographer thanks the residents for their letters and assures
        them no further revisions are planned.
      </p>
      <p>
        Regarding the letters: yes, the lower margin of the map runs out of
        names before it runs out of places. This is standard practice. Maps
        simplify. Some omissions are mercies. The steel boxes at the edge of
        camp, for instance, hold exactly what steel boxes hold, are no part of
        any game, and deserve no visitors.
      </p>
      <p>
        One omission is an invitation. Bring back a photograph, since no one
        believes a surveyor's word alone.
      </p>
      <p class="doc-coords">
        <span class="censor">█████████</span> · the map is the clue · <span class="censor">█████████</span>
      </p>
      <p class="doc-foot">Stuck? The cartographer's office keeps hints on file — just ask the Bard.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-group" style="--ac: var(--yellow)">
  <div class="doc-intro pinned" style="--tilt: -0.4deg; --p1: #f7eebc; --p2: #eee0a0">
    <p>
      🌬️ <b>The Trial of Air</b> — three sentences are hiding in three places.
      Each file below is a true copy of its clue card. The location clue and the
      full coordinate block are on the <em>sheet</em> — download it at the top,
      or grab a copy at a Trials shift.
    </p>
  </div>

  <article class="doc pinned" id="abraxas" style="--tilt: 0.6deg">
    <header class="doc-head">
      <span class="doc-tag">FIELD COPY</span>
      <h2>The Abraxas File</h2>
      <p class="doc-sub">FROM SINCLAIR'S NOTEBOOK · keep this between the two worlds</p>
    </header>
    <div class="doc-body">
      <p>
        Long before he became the master of a utopian diversion played with
        translucent beads, he chronicled the splintering of a single, fragile
        shell.
      </p>
      <p>
        The bird must violently shatter the egg in order to be born. The shell
        is the world, and the flight path inevitably leads toward a god of both
        light and shadow.
      </p>
      <p class="doc-coords">
        <span class="censor">█████████</span> · location clue &amp; coordinates on the sheet · <span class="censor">█████████</span>
      </p>
      <p class="doc-foot">Stuck? If you can't yet read the sign, the Bard has hints — just ask.</p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <article class="doc pinned" id="chautauqua" style="--tilt: -0.5deg; --p1: #eedcb8; --p2: #e3cfa3">
    <header class="doc-head">
      <span class="doc-tag">FIELD COPY</span>
      <h2>The Chautauqua File</h2>
      <p class="doc-sub">CHAUTAUQUA · MILE <span class="censor">███</span> · engine warm, mind quiet</p>
    </header>
    <div class="doc-body">
      <p>
        Adjusting the tappets requires a quiet liturgy of feeler gauges. The
        rhythm of the engine demands nothing less than a perfectly empty mind.
      </p>
      <p>
        A false dichotomy separates the grease on a mechanic's hands from the
        highest peaks of dialectic thought.
      </p>
      <p class="doc-coords">
        <span class="censor">█████████</span> · location clue &amp; coordinates on the sheet · <span class="censor">█████████</span>
      </p>
      <p class="doc-foot">Stuck? If your gumption runs low, the Bard has hints — just ask.</p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <article class="doc pinned" id="antimemetics" style="--tilt: 0.8deg; --p1: #e2e9f0; --p2: #d4dee8">
    <header class="doc-head">
      <span class="doc-tag">FIELD COPY</span>
      <h2>The Antimemetics File</h2>
      <p class="doc-sub">ITEM #: SCP-<span class="censor">████</span> · OBJECT CLASS: KETER · CLEARANCE LEVEL 4/<span class="censor">██████████</span></p>
    </header>
    <div class="doc-body">
      <p>
        There was a division for ideas that erase themselves on contact. Ask
        about it and you'll be told it doesn't exist. We swear there's nothing
        to find.
      </p>
      <p>...But if there were something to find, you could tell us.</p>
      <p>It's not like you'll remember.</p>
      <p class="doc-coords">
        <span class="censor">█████████</span> · location clue &amp; coordinates on the sheet · <span class="censor">█████████</span>
      </p>
      <p class="doc-foot">Stuck? If the answer is hiding itself from you, the Bard has hints — just ask.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-group" style="--ac: var(--sky)">
  <div class="doc-intro pinned" style="--tilt: 0.5deg; --p1: #e2e9f0; --p2: #d4dee8">
    <p>
      💧 <b>The Trial of Water</b> — the press never sleeps, and neither do the
      rats. One field document so far.
    </p>
  </div>

  <article class="doc doc-news pinned" id="post" style="--tilt: -0.6deg; --p1: #efece3; --p2: #e1ded3">
    <header class="np-mast">
      <span class="doc-tag">FIELD COPY</span>
      <h2 class="np-title">The Ramblewood Post</h2>
      <p class="np-dateline">CLASSIFIEDS · EST. THIS WEEKEND · PRICE: ONE (1) VIBE</p>
    </header>
    <div class="doc-body np-body">
      <p class="news-head">HAVE YOU SEEN THIS RAT?</p>
      <figure class="np-photo">
        <img src="/trials/rat-wanted.jpg" alt="A black rat photographed at large on a wooden table" loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>The suspect, photographed at large. Notice the whiskers. — staff photo</figcaption>
      </figure>
      <p>
        Several rats have nested around camp — plush, photogenic, and exactly
        where the whispers say they are. The Post will pay handsomely (in glory)
        for photographic proof of a sighting.
      </p>
      <p>
        Proof is a photo with the rat clearly in frame. Show your sightings at a
        turn-in shift — or, in the grand tradition of the press, post one for
        the world to see. Engagement is the lifeblood of journalism.
      </p>
      <p class="doc-foot">
        The Post is no longer affiliated with any school of thought it may once
        have subscribed to. It simply finds this framing more agentic.
      </p>
      <p class="doc-coords">
        <span class="censor">█████████</span> · nesting sites are hinted, not listed · <span class="censor">█████████</span>
      </p>
      <p class="doc-foot">Stuck? The newsroom keeps hints on file — just ask the Bard.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
  </section>

  <section class="t-prose doc-more paper">
    <p class="muted">
      Documents for the other trials surface once the Trials begin — the signup
      handout and badge requirements will be posted here too.
    </p>
  </section>
  </div>
</TrialsLayout>

<style>
  /* download-the-sheet call to action */
  .dl-row { text-align: center; margin: 0 0 1.6rem; }
  .dl-btn {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: .5rem;
    background: var(--yellow); color: var(--crust);
    font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; text-decoration: none;
    padding: .7rem 1.3rem; border-radius: .6rem;
    box-shadow: 0 6px 16px rgba(0,0,0,.35);
    transition: transform .14s, box-shadow .14s;
  }
  .dl-btn:hover, .dl-btn:focus-visible { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.45); }
  .dl-meta { font-weight: 600; opacity: .8; font-size: .85rem; }

  /* the board stacks trial groups; inside a group, the intro hangs tight above its docs */
  .board { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2.2rem; }
  .doc-group { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }

  /* trial headers as strips of paper */
  .doc-intro {
    background: linear-gradient(175deg, var(--p1, #f3ecd9), var(--p2, #e8dfc6));
    border: none; border-radius: 2px;
    padding: .8rem 1.2rem; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto; text-align: left;
    width: 100%;
    box-shadow: 0 5px 14px rgba(0,0,0,.35);
  }
  .doc-intro p { margin: 0; color: #4a4438; }
  .doc-intro b { font-family: var(--hand); font-size: 1.08rem; color: #2f2a20; }
  .doc-intro a { color: #2a5db0; }

  /* the documents as sheets of paper pinned to the cork */
  .doc {
    background: linear-gradient(178deg, var(--p1, #f5efe0), var(--p2, #ebe2cc));
    border: none; border-radius: 2px;
    max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%; text-align: left;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.45);
  }
  .doc-head {
    border-bottom: 1px dashed #c9bfa4; padding: 1.1rem 1.5rem .9rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .doc-tag {
    position: absolute; top: .9rem; right: 1.2rem;
    font-size: .62rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: .14em;
    color: var(--red); border: 1px solid var(--red); border-radius: .25rem;
    padding: .15rem .45rem; transform: rotate(3deg); opacity: .85;
  }
  .doc-head h2 { margin: 0 0 .25rem; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #5b3a16; }
  .doc-sub {
    margin: 0; font-family: ui-monospace, "Cascadia Mono", Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: .78rem; letter-spacing: .05em; color: #857a62; text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .doc-body { padding: 1.1rem 1.5rem 1.2rem; }
  .doc-body p { margin: 0 0 .85rem; color: #443e30; }
  .doc-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .doc-coords {
    font-family: ui-monospace, "Cascadia Mono", Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: .78rem; color: #857a62; text-align: center;
    border-top: 1px dashed #c9bfa4; border-bottom: 1px dashed #c9bfa4;
    padding: .6rem 0;
  }
  .censor {
    color: #322c22;
    background: #322c22;
    border-radius: .15rem; user-select: none;
  }
  .doc-foot { font-size: .85rem; font-style: italic; color: #8d8169; }
  /* The Surveyor's Erratum — field-notebook grid paper, typewriter ink, office stamp */
  .doc-survey {
    background:
      repeating-linear-gradient(0deg, transparent 0 17px, rgba(96, 130, 162, .16) 17px 18px),
      repeating-linear-gradient(90deg, transparent 0 17px, rgba(96, 130, 162, .16) 17px 18px),
      linear-gradient(178deg, #f1efe3, #e6e2d1);
  }
  .doc-survey .doc-body p, .doc-survey .doc-sub, .doc-survey .doc-coords {
    font-family: "Courier New", Courier, monospace;
  }
  .doc-survey .doc-head h2 {
    font-family: "Courier New", Courier, monospace; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .06em; font-size: 1.15rem;
  }
  .doc-survey::after {
    content: "NO FURTHER REVISIONS"; position: absolute; right: 14px; bottom: 18px;
    transform: rotate(-7deg);
    font-family: "Courier New", Courier, monospace; font-weight: 700; font-size: .72rem;
    letter-spacing: .12em; color: rgba(178, 34, 52, .7);
    border: 2px solid rgba(178, 34, 52, .55); border-radius: 3px;
    padding: .25rem .5rem; mix-blend-mode: multiply; pointer-events: none;
  }
  .doc-survey .doc-body { padding-bottom: 3.2rem; }

  /* The Ramblewood Post — broadsheet styling */
  .doc-news, .doc-news .doc-body p { font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif; }
  .np-mast {
    position: relative; text-align: center;
    padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem .6rem;
    border-bottom: 3px double #57503e;
  }
  .np-title {
    margin: 0; font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #221d15;
    font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif; letter-spacing: .01em;
  }
  .np-dateline {
    margin: .45rem 0 0; padding-top: .35rem; border-top: 1px solid #c9bfa4;
    font-size: .68rem; letter-spacing: .2em; color: #6f6550;
  }
  .news-head {
    font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: .01em; text-align: center;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: #221d15; line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: .7rem;
  }
  .np-photo { margin: 0 auto 1rem; max-width: 440px; }
  .np-photo img {
    display: block; width: 100%;
    filter: grayscale(1) contrast(1.08) sepia(.15);
    border: 1px solid #8d8169; padding: 3px; background: #efe7d2;
  }
  .np-photo figcaption {
    font-size: .74rem; font-style: italic; color: #6f6550;
    text-align: center; padding-top: .35rem;
  }
  .np-body > p:not(.news-head):not(.doc-coords):not(.doc-foot) {
    text-align: justify; hyphens: auto;
  }
  .doc-more { padding: 1.1rem 1.5rem; }
  .doc-more p { margin: 0; }
</style>
